The paper discusses a method for embedding differentiable optimization problems within deep learning architectures, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a new approach to differentiating through disciplined convex programs, which is a topic that falls under the broader category of optimization (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
